event.title: Royal University of Phnom Penh (RUPP):
event.description: Connect with our advisors virtually, gaining personalized insights and guidance from the comfort of your own space. Seamlessly schedule one-on-one meetings or group sessions, discussing your queries and goals in an interactive online environment.

detail.title: DUIS AUTE IRURE DOLOR IN REPREHENDERIT
detail.description: As a librarian, there are certain moments that stick with me. When one of my students unexpectedly gave me a mutinous look, I knew it was the start of one of them.

detail.title: DUIS AUTE IRURE DOLOR IN REPREHENDERIT
detail.description: Bobby had always been an affable student, but one day when I asked him to return the book he had been reading, he gave me the look. At first, I didn’t understand. It was a small ask after all. The book was brand new, one I hadn’t catalogued or even stamped with the school’s name yet. It was not ready to be loaned out.

detail.title: DUIS AUTE IRURE DOLOR IN REPREHENDERIT
detail.description: It turns out, I had inadvertently stumbled upon something special. Bobby, like all the 8th grade students in our school that year, was reading The Outsiders by S.E. Hinton. I just had received several copies of the title in large print so I asked Bobby to switch from reading his regular print to the larger text. I was curious to see if he would notice any difference between the two formats. Bobby obliged and spent the rest of the period quietly reading, but when the bell rang and it was time to return the book that’s when he gave me the look.
